<p><strong>Saving Throws</strong> Wis +3</p>

<p><strong>Skills</strong> Insight +3, Intimidation +4, Perception +3</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Orc</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 4 (1,100 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Aggressive.</em></strong> As a bonus action, the orc can move up to its speed toward a hostile creature that it can see.</p>

<p><strong><em>Foe Smiter of Ilneval.</em></strong> The orc deals an extra die of damage when it hits with a longsword attack (included in the attack).</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The orc makes two melee attacks with its longsword or two ranged attacks with its javelins. If Ilnevalâ€™s Command is available to use, the orc can use it after these attacks.</p>

<p><strong><em>Longsword.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 12 (2d8+3) slashing damage, or 14 (2d10+3) slashing damage when used with two hands.</p>

<p><strong><em>Javelin.</em></strong> Melee or Ranged Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft. or range 30/120 ft., one target. Hit: 6 (1d6+3) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Ilnevalâ€™s Command (Recharges 4-6).</em></strong> Up to three allied orcs within 120 feet of this orc that can hear it can use their reactions to each make one weapon attack.</p>

